<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Wentzel, Willard Ferdinand. A Continuation of the Journal of the Forks Mackenzie's River for Summer 1807-1808. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0022</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p></p>
<p class="head">July Cont<sup>d</sup> 1808</p>
<p>Gave 67<sup>lb</sup> of Dried meat for their expeditions<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  No Fish<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thurs<sup>y</sup> 8<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Gummed the inside of the Canoe &amp; layed in the varangues<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  4 Fish in the nets<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p>Friday 9<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Banded the Canoe<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  2 P<sup>s</sup> Fish caught<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p>Satur<sup>y</sup> &amp; Sun<sup>y</sup> 11<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Nothing Particular<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  3 Fish<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Mon<sup>y</sup> 12<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Cadien Busy mending his own Canoe<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Martin is now an invalid, occasioned by the pain in his Side<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tues<sup>y</sup> to Thurs<sup>y</sup> 15<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Cadien has finished his Canoe, &amp; is now mending his sail; Martin is pounding meat<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  We have taken no Fish since mon<sup>y</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">16<sup>th</sup> to Sun<sup>y</sup> 18<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[N]</span>othing occurred worth mentioning &#8211; except that on Friday we saw a great Smoke rising in the Forks at very little distance inland &#8211; which gives me great anxiety as I fear that has been Kindled by some of the Indians that I had sent to the Beaver Country in the Spring &#8211; who perhaps have met with the Red Knives &amp; have run away notwithstanding their promises to the <span class="DelHand-author">Country</span> Contrary when they sett off<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[B]</span>esides this we percieved three other smokes in different directions tho' none to allarm me so much as the former<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">19<sup>th</sup> to 21<sup>st</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Employed in searching little rivers to take Fish, without success &#8211; for it now plays hard upon me for prov<sup>ns</sup> &#8211; Altho' we all mess out of the same Kettle &amp; makes but a meal a day &#8211; one half of which consists of Turnip Tops &#8211; to which I now &amp; then out of shame Sake I am obliged to add a Small bit of Grease<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afternoon Cassant &amp; Forcier returned from M<sup>r</sup> Keiths they brought 8 Bales of Dried meat, 1 Keg Gurtons, 1 Keg Gum, 2 Packs of furrs, 20 moose deer Snares &amp; 3 Dress'd Skins &#8211; besides 14<sup>lb</sup> Tob<sup>o</sup> &amp; 8<sup>lb</sup> of gunpowder which I had requested of M<sup>r</sup> Keith to send for the use of the Forks, where we are entirely out of both<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey left Beskawgha Fort the day before yesterday<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">S<span class="DelHand-author">un</span><span class="AddHand-author">at</span><sup>y</sup> 24<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[Y]</span>ester<sup>y</sup> &amp; to day the men <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[e]</span>mployed in pounding the bales of meat<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[L]</span>a<span class="AddHand-editors">[te]</span>ly bro<span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[46]</span></p>

